-- India, Iran Pledge to Cooperate on Renewable Energy Development
-- B y   N a t a l i e   O b i k o   P e a r s o n
-- 2012-03-05T13:52:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-05/india-iran-pledge-to-cooperate-on-renewable-energy-development.html
India  and  Iran  have agreed to
cooperate in promoting renewable energy, the Indian government
said in a press release.  Iranian Energy Minister Majid Namjou said the country
planned to develop clean energy projects with India’s help after
meeting Indian Renewable Energy Minister Farooq Abdullah in
Tehran, according to the e-mailed statement today. It didn’t
provide further details.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Natalie Obiko Pearson in Mumbai at 
 npearson7@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
